Wake up

We typically die earlier than we'd like. I figure that I'll roar towards that inevitable day with a proactive prolonging of time by waking myself up at 5:00 AM. Voluntarily getting up earlier than you have to and at five a.m., much less, is crazy and in my crazed state I feel intensely.

Soup and Salad

The idea of soup and salad is metaphorically ambiguous. What has come up for you in the past when someone offers you the words soup and salad? Let me guess, "No thanks, I just want to get to my main course if you don't mind." There is something more to explore here.
Spencer Harber / Medium

Mind

When I sit alone and ponder

All those deeds of virtuous honor

To downpour answers from the sky

Satisfying that eternal question, “Why”

My mind plays a cunning game

Influencing decisions that keep me the same.

Like a gangster fitting me with cement shoes

To drown me in the dark river of my “dues”

I’ve got to break through and accept life’s offer

No matter the fear and pain felt from father.

I want to do right and I see it in lights:

Helping all others, lifts you to new heights.
